div.p: Load CR3 Set CR0.PG Far Jump Reload Segments
CRITICAL: Between mov cr0 and jmp, code executes in undefined state. The instruction at the jump target MUST be identity-mapped or CPU will triple fault.
mov eax, page_dir_addr mov cr3, eax
Loads page directory base address into CR3 register. TLB is flushed on CR3 write.
mov eax, cr0 or eax, 0x80000000 mov cr0, eax
Sets bit 31 (PG) to enable paging. CPU is now in paged mode but CS still has old selector.
Flushes pipeline and loads CS with protected-mode selector. CRITICAL: code MUST be identity-mapped!
mov ax, 0x10 mov ds, ax mov es, ax mov fs, ax mov gs, ax mov ss, ax
Load all data segment registers with kernel data selector (index 2).
